- Colin: LET'S GO, YOU GUYS.
- HUH?

75
00:05:36,083 --> 00:05:38,000
- WHAT ARE YOU TWO DOING
STANDING AROUND?

76
00:05:38,083 --> 00:05:40,291
THE LECTURE'S ABOUT TO START
AND WE CAN'T BE LATE.

77
00:05:40,375 --> 00:05:41,833
- JUST CATCH UP WITH US, OKAY?

78
00:05:41,916 --> 00:05:45,250
- WAIT, WE'RE COMING
WITH YOU GUYS. LET'S GO.

79
00:05:47,875 --> 00:05:50,208
- OH, MAN. I BLEW IT.

80
00:05:50,291 --> 00:05:52,291
- COME ON, CEDIE!
WE'RE GOING TO BE LATE!

81
00:05:52,375 --> 00:05:53,666
- COMING!

82
00:06:05,583 --> 00:06:07,083
- I'LL SEE YOU SOON, BROTHER.

83
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:12,083
- WITH THE DISCOVERY
OF MERCURION,

84
00:06:12,166 --> 00:06:14,791
MANKIND HAS GAINED THE
MEANS TO DO THE IMPOSSIBLE.

85
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:16,541
APPROACH THE SPEED OF LIGHT.

86
00:06:16,625 --> 00:06:19,083
THE WARS THAT HAVE OCCURRED
DUE TO TERRITORIAL EXPANSION

87
00:06:19,166 --> 00:06:21,583
HAVE CAUSED A RIFT
WITHIN THE HUMAN RACE.

88
00:06:21,666 --> 00:06:23,000
MANY YEARS HAVE PASSED

89
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:25,500
SINCE THE FIRST SPARKS OF
WAR WERE SEEN BETWEEN US,

90
00:06:25,583 --> 00:06:27,375
THE UNION AND THE DEAGUE.

91
00:06:27,458 --> 00:06:29,208
SINCE THEN,
WAR HAS UNFORTUNATELY

92
00:06:29,291 --> 00:06:31,875
BECOME AN INTEGRAL
PART OF HUMAN HISTORY.

93
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:34,541
MAINTAINING OUR EXTENDED
BATTLE LINES

94
00:06:34,625 --> 00:06:36,666
REQUIRES CEASELESS
TECHNOLOGICAL INNOVATION

95
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:38,541
AND THE PINNACLE OF MANPOWER.

96
00:06:38,625 --> 00:06:40,291
THE FIRST BEING THE STRAINS,

97
00:06:40,375 --> 00:06:43,208
FOLLOWED CLOSELY BY
YOU, THE REASONERS.

98
00:06:43,291 --> 00:06:46,458
HOWEVER WE ARE NOT SCIENTISTS,
SO WE CANNOT WIN THIS WAR

99
00:06:46,541 --> 00:06:48,375
WITH TECHNOLOGICAL FEATS ALONE.

100
00:06:48,458 --> 00:06:50,833
BUT WHAT WE CAN DO
IS HONE OUR SKILLS.

101
00:06:50,916 --> 00:06:53,000
AS YOU ARE SOME OF THE
MOST TALENTED REASONERS

102
00:06:53,083 --> 00:06:54,125
TO EVER WALK THESE FABLED HALLS.

103
00:06:54,208 --> 00:06:56,791
- HEY, MARY.
- YEAH, WHAT IS IT, COLIN?

104
00:06:56,875 --> 00:07:00,875
- SO, WITH THOSE TWO, ARE THEY
STILL AVOIDING THE INEVITABLE?

105
00:07:00,958 --> 00:07:03,958
- I DON'T KNOW. IT DOESN'T
LOOK LIKE MUCH IS HAPPENING.

106
00:07:04,041 --> 00:07:06,666
- WHAT IS WITH CEDIE? HE JUST
NEEDS TO ASK HER ALREADY.

107
00:07:06,750 --> 00:07:08,083
- YEAH, BUT THE THING IS,

108
00:07:08,166 --> 00:07:09,500
ALL SARA THINKS
ABOUT IS HER BROTHER,

109
00:07:09,583 --> 00:07:11,083
SO IT'S NOT GOING
TO BE EASY FOR HIM.

110
00:07:12,125 --> 00:07:14,375
- TAKE RALPH WEREC FOR EXAMPLE.

111
00:07:14,458 --> 00:07:17,916
HE IS THE FINEST REASONER EVER
TO GRADUATE FROM THIS ACADEMY.

112
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,833
IN THE BATTLE FOR ALABOMERIS,

113
00:07:19,916 --> 00:07:21,666
HE SHOT DOWN TEN
DEAGUE WARSHIPS,

114
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:23,333
AND WAS THE YOUNGEST PERSON EVER

115
00:07:23,416 --> 00:07:26,500
TO BE GIVEN A GLOIRE
STRAIN FOR USE IN COMBAT.

116
00:07:27,791 --> 00:07:30,083
WHAT WE NEED MOST
ARE REASONERS LIKE HIM,

117
00:07:30,166 --> 00:07:32,875
WHO HAVE BOTH THE GUTS AND
THE SKILL TO WIN THIS WAR.

118
00:07:32,958 --> 00:07:35,958
WITH THEM WE WILL BE ABLE
TO TURN THE TIDE OF THE WAR

119
00:07:36,041 --> 00:07:38,333
AND ACHIEVE VICTORY
FOR OUR PEOPLE.

120
00:07:42,791 --> 00:07:45,958
- ( grunts ) OKAY, HERE WE GO.

121
00:07:46,041 --> 00:07:47,166
- HEY, WAIT UP!

122
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:49,250
( exhales )

123
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:51,166
- WOW! BARELY MADE IT.

124
00:07:52,250 --> 00:07:53,208
- SORRY.

125
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:58,083
- Colin: I CAN'T WAIT UNTIL
I'M JUST LIKE SARA'S BROTHER.

126
00:07:59,250 --> 00:08:00,750
- IT WON'T BE LONG NOW.

127
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:03,916
THERE ARE ONLY TWENTY FLIGHT
HOURS LEFT UNTIL WE GRADUATE.

128
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,916
- AND THEN IT'S ON
TO SUB-LIGHT SPEED.

129
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:09,833
- YEAH. I CAN HARDLY WAIT
TO SEE MY BIG BROTHER AGAIN.

130
00:08:09,916 --> 00:08:11,500
- DID YOU HEAR WHAT
SHE JUST SAID, CEDIE?

131
00:08:11,583 --> 00:08:14,250
IT'S GOING TO BE AN UPHILL
BATTLE, IF YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

132
00:08:14,333 --> 00:08:15,791
- COLIN, WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

133
00:08:15,875 --> 00:08:17,166
- SARA WOULDN'T...
- EXCUSE ME?

134
00:08:18,208 --> 00:08:19,208
- IT'S NOTHING.

135
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:23,208
- HEY, LOOK. IT'S HIGGINS.

136
00:08:23,291 --> 00:08:25,416
- Colin: I HEARD HE
ACCIDENTALLY DAMAGED HIS MIMIC

137
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:27,000
IN A TRAINING EXERCISE.

138
00:08:32,333 --> 00:08:33,583
I WONDER WHAT HE'S
GOING TO DO NOW.

139
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:38,208
- Havisham: LISTEN UP!

140
00:08:38,291 --> 00:08:40,750
YOUR MIMIC CONTAINS CULTURED
BRAIN CELLS THAT WERE HARVESTED

141
00:08:40,833 --> 00:08:42,291
FROM EACH AND EVERY ONE OF YOU

142
00:08:42,375 --> 00:08:44,750
WHILE YOU WERE STILL FLOATING
INSIDE YOUR MOTHER'S BELLY!

143
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:47,166
LOOK AT IT THIS WAY.
YOUR MIMIC IS YOUR TWIN.

144
00:08:47,250 --> 00:08:50,125
ONCE IT DIES,
IT WILL NEVER COME BACK!

145
00:08:50,208 --> 00:08:52,166
IF YOU EVER LOSE OR
DAMAGE YOUR MIMIC,

146
00:08:52,250 --> 00:08:54,708
YOU WILL NO LONGER HAVE
THE ABILITY TO BE A REASONER.

147
00:08:54,791 --> 00:08:57,583
THEN YOU'D BE USELESS TO ME!

148
00:08:57,666 --> 00:08:59,958
THAT'S WHY YOU MUST TAKE
BETTER CARE OF YOUR MIMIC

149
00:09:00,041 --> 00:09:01,041
THAN YOU DO OF YOURSELF!

150
00:09:01,125 --> 00:09:03,041
WE CAN REPLACE A LIMB EASILY,

151
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:06,583
BUT WE CANNOT
REPLACE YOUR MIMIC!

152
00:09:06,666 --> 00:09:09,916
TOO SLOW! I'LL BE SEEING YOU IN
THE WORK FIELDS FOR DETENTION!

153
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:12,250
WHO'S NEXT! SHOW ME SOME EFFORT!

154
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:13,750
- PRETTY SOON WE WON'T HAVE TO

155
00:09:13,833 --> 00:09:16,458
LISTEN TO DICTATOR HAVISHAM'S
PEARLS OF WISDOM ANYMORE.

156
00:09:16,541 --> 00:09:18,958
- THE BEST WAY TO DEAL
WITH HIM IS TO IGNORE HIM.

157
00:09:19,041 --> 00:09:20,375
- I HEARD YOU!

158
00:09:20,458 --> 00:09:22,500
DOES ANYONE KNOW WHAT I
HAVE TO SAY ABOUT THAT?

159
00:09:22,583 --> 00:09:25,541
- SIR, "SLACKERS IN TRAINING
MAKE MISTAKES IN WAR".

160
00:09:25,625 --> 00:09:27,541
IS THAT RIGHT,
INSTRUCTOR HAVISHAM?

161
00:09:27,625 --> 00:09:30,791
- ( grunts ) YES.
THAT'S CORRECT.

162
00:09:30,875 --> 00:09:34,625
- ( all giggle )

163
00:09:34,708 --> 00:09:37,416
- YOU KNOW, YOU KIDS ARE
SOME OF THE BEST PROSPECTS

164
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:38,416
I'VE SEEN IN YEARS.

165
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:40,000
IF YOU KEEP GOING AT THIS RATE,

166
00:09:40,083 --> 00:09:43,250
YOU'LL SURPASS THE ABILITIES
OF RALPH WEREC IN NO TIME.

167
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:45,250
THAT'S ESPECIALLY
TRUE FOR YOU, SARA.

168
00:09:45,333 --> 00:09:46,500
SO KEEP WORKING HARD,

169
00:09:46,583 --> 00:09:48,416
SO YOUR BROTHER DOESN'T
LEAVE YOU IN HIS DUST.

170
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:49,458
- ( gasps )

171
00:09:50,041 --> 00:09:51,000
YES, SIR.

172
00:09:51,708 --> 00:09:53,208
- ( exhales )

173
00:09:53,291 --> 00:09:56,083
- I'M GUESSING YOU NEVER
MANAGED TO ASK SARA OUT.

174
00:09:56,166 --> 00:09:58,083
- THE TIMING NEVER
SEEMED TO WORK OUT.

175
00:09:58,166 --> 00:09:59,916
- IT'S HARD TO DO WHEN
ALL SHE EVER THINKS ABOUT

176
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,125
IS HER BROTHER, YOU KNOW?

177
00:10:02,208 --> 00:10:03,916
REMEMBER, ONCE WE GRADUATE,

178
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,916
WE'LL ALL BE ASSIGNED TO
DIFFERENT SQUADRONS.

179
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,208
YOU'RE RUNNING OUT OF TIME.

180
00:10:07,291 --> 00:10:09,250
- YEAH, I'M AWARE OF THAT.
THANKS, MARY.

181
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:10,166
- HEY.
- HUH?

182
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:11,708
WHAT'RE YOU GUYS
TALKING ABOUT?

183
00:10:11,791 --> 00:10:13,958
- SARA! WE WEREN'T
TALKING ABOUT ANYTHING!

184
00:10:14,041 --> 00:10:15,958
- THE TRUTH IS,
CEDIE WANTS TO...

185
00:10:16,041 --> 00:10:17,666
- AH, NO, DON'T!

186
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:20,333
- WELL? YOU'RE NOT JUST GOING
TO LEAVE ME HANGING ARE YOU?

187
00:10:20,416 --> 00:10:21,833
- OH. WELL, UH...

188
00:10:21,916 --> 00:10:22,875
( exhales )

189
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:25,625
- COME ON, TELL ME.

190
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:29,041
- ( both ) WELL, WE'D LIKE TO.
- WHAT IS GOING ON?

191
00:10:34,291 --> 00:10:36,291
- ( music box playing )

192
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:46,416
- IT WON'T BE LONG NOW, BROTHER.

193
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:47,583
I'LL BE ABLE TO TRAVEL TO

194
00:10:47,666 --> 00:10:50,125
WHEREVER IN THE GALAXY
YOU ARE STATIONED,

195
00:10:50,208 --> 00:10:51,208
AND THEN...

196
00:10:51,291 --> 00:10:52,250
- ( footsteps approaching )

197
00:10:54,333 --> 00:10:55,791
- I SEE YOU'VE SNUCK
OUT OF THE DORMS

198
00:10:55,875 --> 00:10:57,041
IN THE MIDDLE OF
THE NIGHT AGAIN.

199
00:10:57,125 --> 00:10:59,083
DON'T BLAME ME
IF THEY YELL AT YOU.

200
00:10:59,166 --> 00:11:01,291
- I'M NOT CONCERNED
WITH BEING YELLED AT.

201
00:11:01,375 --> 00:11:02,791
BESIDES, A LITTLE FRESH AIR IS

202
00:11:02,875 --> 00:11:04,416
WORTH WHATEVER
PUNISHMENT I MAY GET.

203
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:07,083
PLUS, WHENEVER I'M UP HERE
I GET TO GAZE AT THE STARS,

204
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:09,166
WHICH HELPS ME FEEL
CLOSER TO MY BROTHER.

205
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:11,000
- AGAIN WITH YOUR BROTHER?

206
00:11:11,083 --> 00:11:13,125
YOU MUST HAVE
A LOT OF LOVE FOR HIM.

207
00:11:13,208 --> 00:11:15,000
MAKES ME JEALOUS.

208
00:11:15,083 --> 00:11:18,208
- WELL, OF COURSE I LOVE HIM.
HE'S THE ONLY BROTHER I HAVE.

209
00:11:19,583 --> 00:11:20,541
- TRUE.

210
00:11:24,458 --> 00:11:27,166
- CEDIE, DANCE WITH ME.
- UH...

211
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:29,875
- LET'S SEE IF YOU'VE GOTTEN
ANY BETTER AT THE BOX STEP.

212
00:11:32,541 --> 00:11:34,208
- JUST BE GENTLE, I'M NO EXPERT.

213
00:11:44,125 --> 00:11:46,458
- EASY CEDIE, NOT SO FAST!

214
00:11:46,541 --> 00:11:48,291
- I GUESS I'VE GOTTEN
BETTER THAN I THOUGHT.

215
00:11:48,375 --> 00:11:50,250
THE LEAST YOU CAN DO
IS COMPLIMENT ME.

216
00:11:50,333 --> 00:11:51,625
- YOU KNOW I CAN'T DO THAT

217
00:11:51,708 --> 00:11:53,291
BECAUSE THEN I'D
BE PAMPERING YOU.

218
00:11:53,375 --> 00:11:55,333
- I CAN ONLY DO THE BEST I CAN,

219
00:11:55,416 --> 00:11:56,958
IT'S JUST TOO BAD THAT
IT WILL NEVER BE AS GOOD

220
00:11:57,041 --> 00:11:58,375
AS SOMEONE'S PERFECT BROTHER.

221
00:11:58,458 --> 00:12:00,125
- THAT'S OBVIOUS, ISN'T IT?

222
00:12:00,208 --> 00:12:02,500
( gasps ) SORRY.

223
